(956, 9, 'inproceedings', 'Lifschitz08', 'Answer set programming (ASP) is a form of declarative pro- gramming oriented towards difficult search problems. As an outgrowth of research on the use of nonmonotonic reason- ing in knowledge representation, it is particularly useful in knowledge-intensive applications. ASP programs consist of rules that look like Prolog rules, but the computational mech- anisms used in ASP are different: they are based on the ideas that have led to the creation of fast satisfiability solvers for propositional logic.', 'Vladimir Lifschitz', 'AAAI', NULL, 'DBLP:conf/aaai/2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1594-1597', NULL, NULL, 'What Is Answer Set Programming?', NULL, '2008'),
