(270, 1, 'article', 'Anton07', 'A framework supporting the privacy policy life cycle helps guide the kind of research to consider before sound privacy answers may be realized\n\nInformation technology advances are making Internet and Web-based system use the common choice in many application domains, ranging from business to health care to scientific collaboration and distance learning. However, adoption is slowed by well-founded concerns about privacy, especially given that data collected about individuals is being combined with information from other sources and analyzed by powerful tools (such as data mining tools).', 'Annie I. Ant\\''{o}n and Elisa Bertino and Ninghui Li and Ting Yu', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/1272516.1272522', NULL, 'Commun. ACM', NULL, '109--116', 'ACM', NULL, 'A roadmap for comprehensive online privacy policy management', '50', '2007'),
